    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Writing out the pure Python doesn't mean it doesn't use IPython, it just means it doesn't use IPython's syntax.\nFor instance, in the transformed history, `%timeit time.sleep(0)` is actually `get_ipython().magic(u'timeit time.sleep(0)')`.  This is what we should write to a .py file, not the IPython syntax, which is not valid Python.\n"
  },
