    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Ok, that makes sense :)\nSo, when I set my ipython notebook to create a .py script (through the --script option), why doesn't ipython notebook write get_ipython().magic(u'timeit time.sleep(0)')? Instead, I get a script that would have: %timeit time.sleep(0). This .py file can't be run by python, and ipython won't run it as a magic command unless it has the .ipy extension. This is why I was trying to rename it and wishing that ipython notebook would do this for me.\nAm I missing something?\n"
